# MMS connection phase — ACSE AARQ (Associate Request), over TPKT/COTP/ISO-Session (CONNECT SPDU).
# Real ICCP/TASE.2 PDU reassembled from a TCP-segmented capture (mms.cap frame 11), re-wrapped in
# eth/IPv4/TCP:102 via the codec. Only the hex is committed. The ISO 8327 CONNECT SPDU (SI 13) carries the
# ISO 8823 Presentation CP-type in its user-data (PGI 0xc1), which wraps the ACSE AARQ (0x60) and the MMS
# initiate-request. The session/ACSE bytes are kept verbatim; only the ACSE APDU type is surfaced (AARQ).

